quote: "The sun, an abbed fool,"
subject: Victorian Nature Poetry (1837–1901)
permalink: /Victorian Nature Poetry (1837–1901)/A E Housman/A E Housman - The Sun
---

The sun, an abbed fool,
Does smile so sweetly,
And cast fair shadows of
The boughs that droop above.

At sunset in the grove
The peasant stops to sigh,
But the stars are dearer—oh,
To those who seek the sky.


- A E Housman
